==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Outlawry
<hw>Out"law`ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Outlawries</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of
outlawing; the putting a man out of the protection of law, or the
process by which a man (as an absconding criminal) is deprived of that
protection.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The state of being an outlaw.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Defiance of the law; habitual criminality.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Outlay</ent>⟦br⟧
